NAME: In a hole beneath the tree
DESCRIPTION: You've managed to crawl down a hole beneath the huge oak tree. Walls of dirt block any movement in any direction, other than up. You can hear insects crawling about all over.

NAME: Climbing a tree
DESCRIPTION: You are climbing the huge oak tree. About 3 feet below you can see the ground. Falling from this height would definitely result in some broken limbs. Best to hold on tight while you are here! Or, if you dare, you can venture further upwards to the top of the oak tree.

NAME: The top of the oak tree
DESCRIPTION: You've reached the top of the giant oak tree. You can now see that the floor of the forest is about 12 feet down. A fall from this height would surely prove fatal, if not at least severely injured.

NAME: Entering a field
DESCRIPTION: You have left the deep jungle, at least for the moment. To the north, you can see what appears to be a large field. You can hear a lot of activity from animals, and possibly even others.
